/tech/Passenger_Car_Series_116.pdf}}</ref> || style=\"text-align:center;\"| W3A&nbsp;040&nbsp;(722.0)<ref name=\"AT-1\"/> || style=\"text-align:center;\"| W3B&nbsp;050&nbsp;(722.0) Worldwide<ref name=\"AT-2\">{{cite web|title=MB Passenger Car Types with Engine M117, PDF p. 14|url=http://img.w116.org/tech/Passenger_Car_Types_with_Engine_M117.pdf}}</ref> W3A&nbsp;040&nbsp;(722.0)&nbsp;USA&nbsp;&&nbsp;Japan<ref name=\"AT-2\"/> || style=\"text-align:center;\"| W3B&nbsp;050&nbsp;reinf.&nbsp;(722.003)<ref name=\"AT-3\">{{cite web|title=MB AUS 1979, PDF p. 57|url=http://img.w116.org/tech/AUS_1979.pdf}}</ref>|| style=\"text-align:center;\"| W4B&nbsp;025&nbsp;(722.1)\n|- \n| Electrical system:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|  12 volt\n|- \n| Front suspension:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Double wishbones, coil and additional rubber springs, stabilising bar <br/> 6.9: Double wishbones, hydropneumatic damping, stabilizing torsion bar\n|- \n| Rear suspension::&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Diagonal swing axle, trailing arms, coil springs, stabilizing torsion bar <br/> 6.9: Diagonal swing axle, hydropneumatic damping, stabilizing torsion bar \u00b7 4.5 and 6.9: starting anti-dive suspension\n|- \n| Brakes:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Disc brakes (\u00d8 278&nbsp;mm front, 279&nbsp;mm rear), power assisted, from 1979 on request [[Anti-lock Braking System|ABS]]\n|- \n| Steering:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Recirculating ball steering, manual or servo-assisted\n|- \n| Body structure:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Sheet steel, monocoque (unibody) construction\n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n| Dry weight:&nbsp; || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|1660|kg|0|abbr=on}} <br/> USA: {{convert|3770|lb|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|1665|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|1700|kg|0|abbr=on}} <br/> USA: {{convert|3750|lb|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|1725|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|1760|kg|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|1740|kg|0|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|1825|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <br/> USA: {{convert|3843|lb|kg|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|1985|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <br/> USA: {{convert|4285|lb|kg|abbr=on}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|1815|kg|lb|abbr=on}} \n|- \n| Loaded weight:&nbsp; || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|2130|kg|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|2130|kg|0|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|2165|kg|lb|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|2195|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|2220|kg|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|2250|kg|0|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|2285|kg|lb|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|2420|kg|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|2215|kg|lb|abbr=on}}\n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n| Track front/<br>rear:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|1521|mm|in|abbr=on}} / {{convert|1505|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n|- \n| Wheelbase:&nbsp; || colspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;\"| S/SE: {{convert|2865|mm|in|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|2965|mm|in|abbr=on}} || colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| SE: {{convert|2860.|mm|in|abbr=on}} <br/> SEL: {{convert|2960.|mm|in|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|2865|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n| Length:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|4960.|mm|in|abbr=on}} <br/> {{convert|5060.|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n|- \n| Width:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|1870.|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n|- \n| Height:&nbsp; || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|1410.|mm|in|abbr=on}} \u2212 {{convert|1430.|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n| Tyre/Tire sizes:&nbsp; || colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| 185 HR 14 || colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| 205/70 VR 14  || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 215/70 VR 14  || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 185 HR 14  \n|- \n|  || colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|- \n| Acceleration 0\u2013100&nbsp;km/h (0-62 mph):&nbsp;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 11.5s || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10.5s || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9.5s (10.0s SEL) || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8.5s  (8.9s SEL) || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7.4s || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 17.0s 16.2s (from 10.1979)\n|- \n| Top speed:&nbsp; || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|190|km/h|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|200|km/h|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|205|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|210|km/h|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|225|km/h|0|abbr=on}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{convert|165|km/h|mph|abbr=on}}\n|- \n| Fuel Consumption (guideline DIN 70030: determined at 3/4 of top-speed (not more than 110&nbsp;km/h), plus 10%):&nbsp; || colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|12.5|l/100 km }} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|13.0|l/100 km }} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|14.5|l/100 km }} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|16.0|l/100 km }} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{convert|10.6|l/100 km }}\n|}\n\n==Features==\n[[File:Marmagne, Sa\u00f4ne-et-Loire - France (6232182844).jpg|thumb|Mercedes-Benz 280 SE (France)]]\n[[File:1973-1980 Mercedes-Benz 450 SEL (V 116) sedan (2016-01-29) 02.jpg|thumb|Mercedes-Benz 450 SEL (Australia)]]\n\nThe W116 S-Class incorporated a broad variety of Mercedes-Benz safety innovations.\n* Four wheel [[anti-lock brakes]] were first featured as an option on the 1978 W116 S-Class. This system prevents the wheels from locking while braking. The system improves steering control during hard braking situations, and to shorten brake distances.\n* Strengthened body structure.  The W116 featured a more stable security passenger cell with a stiffened roof frame structure. High strength roof and door pillars, along with other reinforced zones, provided enhanced vehicle occupant protection.\n* Deformation zones (crumple zones) in the front and rear.\n* A padded dashboard, deformable switches and controls, and a four-spoke steering wheel with impact absorber and broad impact cushion aimed to reduce occupant injury during collisions.\n* The fuel tank was no longer fitted at the rear end, but was now placed above the rear axle for added protection.\n* Wraparound turn signals made it easier to communicate with nearby drivers.\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n\n====General====\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Alder |first=Trevor |title=Mercedes-Benz S-Class Saloons, 1972\u201391: Road Tests & Articles |series= |year=1996 |publisher=Transport Source Books |location=|asin=B005U5LANQ }}\n* {{Barrett-IBG-MB-2}}\n* {{H\u00e4u\u00dfermann-MBS-1952}}\n* {{cite book |last=Hofner |first=Heribert |title=Die S-Klasse von Mercedes-Benz: von der Kultur des Fahrens |trans-title=The S-Class from Mercedes-Benz: from the culture of driving |year=1997 |publisher=Bechterm\u00fcnz Verlag |location=Augsburg |isbn=3-86047-589-4 |language=de}}\n* {{Hofner-Schrader-MBA-2}}\n* {{Kittler-TMB-1}}\n* {{Kittler-TMB-2}}\n* {{Niemann-PvMB}}\n* {{Oswald-MBP-2}}\n* {{R\u00f6cke-GMSK}}\n* {{R\u00f6cke-NGMSK}}\n* {{Schlegelmilch-M-2013}}\n* {{cite book |last=Storz |first=Alexander Franc |title=Mercedes-Benz S-Klasse: Baureihe W 116 |series=Schrader-Typen-Chronik series |year=2010 |publisher=Motorbuch Verlag |location=Stuttgart |isbn=9783613031838 |language=de}}\n* {{Taylor-MB since 1945-3|pages=6\u201322, 61\u201388, 127\u2013129, 133\